{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Modulo Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Modulo Filter</h1>

<p>Returns the remainder after dividing a number by another number.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ number | modulo: divisor }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 10 | modulo: 3 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 1</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 12 | modulo: 4 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 0</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 7 | modulo: 2 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 1</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>This filter uses Go's <code>math.Mod</code> function, which supports floating-point numbers. The sign of the result follows the sign of the dividend.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/divided_by">divided_by</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/times">times</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
